      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"7. OPAWA ELVIS could not have been more impressive last start in his dazzling 16.85 win at this track over 295m. Faces his toughest race to date reaching class 5 company. In form and can measure up again. 5. TWO DOWN was out of placings last time (18.00) at Wanganui in a Class 5 H, finishing fourth and beaten 5 lengths. Will appreciate a return to this track and makes strong appeal on best. 6. SKELETOR was well fancied last time and led throughout to score (22.38) at Ascot Park in a Class 3/4 over 390m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Leading chance again despite rising in class. 8. LADY DAISY profiles nicely over this trip. Enjoys a wide draw.\",\"runners\":[7,5,6,8],\"exclusive\":false}",
